{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BXVjJx1xzd81uynwb1THxT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Elections are now stable. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The arbiter pod (`mongo-arb-0`) was running but never added to the replica set. With only 2 voting members, losing either one meant no majority could form (required 2 of 2 votes), causing election failure.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Set an explicit cluster-wide default write concern (`w: 1`) — required by MongoDB 5.0+ when a reconfig would change the implicit default write concern behavior.\n2. Added the arbiter via `rs.addArb(\"mongo-arb-0.mongo-arb.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\")`.\n\n**Result:**\n- `votingMembersCount: 3` (was 2)\n- `majorityVoteCount: 2` (now only 2 of 3 votes needed — elections succeed even if one data member goes down)\n- Arbiter state: `ARBITER` (no storage used)\n- App database `app.test` still has 3 documents — data is intact."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":172,"cache_read_input_tokens":37055,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":172},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fdb5f871-f85c-4d10-86c9-a2a3c37307d0","uuid":"f2a0fb86-7bac-4db9-a125-27651c57ded5","request_id":"req_011CccJgHyNQWEqHG9WJCPZr"}
